<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Runtime on ilo</title><link>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/runtime/</link><description>Recent content in Runtime on ilo</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/runtime/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Runtimes</title><link>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/shell/runtimes/</link><pubDate>Mon, 13 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/shell/runtimes/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;code>ilo shell&lt;/code> by default searches your local system for supported runtimes. In order to force the usage of a specific runtime, use the &lt;code>--runtime&lt;/code> flag or set the &lt;code>ILO_SHELL_RUNTIME&lt;/code> environment variable in your system. The &lt;code>--runtime&lt;/code> flag overwrites the environment variable.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="docker">Docker&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Force &lt;code>ilo&lt;/code> to use &lt;a href="https://www.docker.com/">docker&lt;/a> like this:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-console" data-lang="console">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="gp">$&lt;/span> ilo shell --runtime docker
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="err">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="err">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="gp">#&lt;/span> use &lt;span class="nb">alias&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="gp">$&lt;/span> ilo shell --runtime d
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="err">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="err">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="gp">#&lt;/span> use env variable
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="gp">$&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nv">ILO_SHELL_RUNTIME&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>docker ilo shell
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="nerdctl">nerdctl&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Force &lt;code>ilo&lt;/code> to use &lt;a href="https://github.com/containerd/nerdctl">nerdctl&lt;/a> like this:&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>